text: Brainerd is a city in Crow Wing County, Minnesota, United States. Its population was 14,395 at the 2020 census. It is the county seat of Crow Wing County, and is one of northern Minnesota's largest cities. The city is famous for the 1996 movie Fargo being partly set there. ==References== Category:Cities in Minnesota Category:County seats in Minnesota
title: Brainerd, Minnesota
